					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Gathering up all GB(C) repro board info in one place.<br /><br />- BitBuilt:<br />---- 2mb + RTC + 32kb SRAM, MBC3, 45$<br />---- other versions too, but their store is down, and google cache only has that<br />- J. Rodrigo:<br />---- 2mb + 32kb FRAM, MBC5, 37.70$<br />---- 4mb + 32kb FRAM, MBC5, 47.20$<br />- BennVenn:<br />---- 2mb + SRAM, MBC1/2/3/5, 20$<br />---- 2mb + FRAM, MBC1/2/3/5, 24$<br />---- 4mb + SRAM, MBC1/2/3/5, 24$<br />---- 4mb + FRAM, MBC1/2/3/5, 28$<br />---- 4mb + SRAM, unknown mapper, 13$<br />- CatSkull (Sheep It Up):<br />---- 32kb, 10$<br /><br />Then there are Chinese Pokemon clones at about 4$, but they come with the usual quality issues, saving issues, wrong voltage parts, etc. Doesn't seem too good right now, even with volume discounts publishing homebrew wouldn't be too tenable. BennVenn's cheaper cart might be ok if it comes with a decent mapper, but his products are out of stock 95% of the time. If I missed an option, please post.<br /><br />Sheep It Up had custom boards made, at least one release used the Pokemon clones, no idea what Tobu Tobu Girl uses. I recall INL saying it'd be nice to get into the Gameboys, competition would be welcome <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /></div>

					
