				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">One of the major problems is that Micron just discontinued their 2 MiB 5V flash, leaving only Macronix with 1 MiB 5V parts (and other vendors of even smaller parts). The carts are small enough that fitting in any voltage translation is tricky.<br /><br />On the other hand, if people were actually going to start making <em>new</em> games rather than moonshine, simple discrete logic mappers with self-flashing and without RAM support are simple, fit easily, and don't provide meaningfully fewer features than the OEM options.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

